{"id":"8003","name":"Log Weight, Waist & Height","tagline":"Simply add your weight, waist or height measurements to Apple Health","icon":"ios14 c4271458815 g59843","latest":"27437","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<h1>Log Weight, Waist &amp; Height</h1>\n<p>Over indulged at Christmas or during your summer holiday? Still growing or just looking to track these key attributes?</p>\n<p>Apple Health doesn’t make it easy to enter these simple details to keep track of your Health stats even though it uses them to calculate many fitness related parameters.</p>\n<p>Log Weight, Waist &amp; Height makes adding your weight, waist or height measurements to Apple Health a lot easier than the native menus!</p>\n<p>Now with the choice of Metric or Imperial/English entry formats!</p>\n<h3>Metric</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Weight - Kilograms (kg)</li>\n<li>Waist - Centimetres (cm)</li>\n<li>Height - Metres (m) and Centimetres (cm)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Imperial / English</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Weight - Stones (st) and Pounds (lb) or Pounds (lb)</li>\n<li>Waist - Inches (in)</li>\n<li>Height - Feet (ft) and Inches (in)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>3 simple steps</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Choose which measurement to add.</li>\n<li>Enter measurement.</li>\n<li>Confirm measurement is correct.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Simple Graphs</h3>\n<p>Want to quickly check your progress or changes over time? \nThere are now simple line graphs available (configurable in the customise shortcut menu) that allows you to view them as a target or average depending on your goals.</p>\n<p><img alt=\"Log Weight, Waist &amp; Height\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/LMbBfI1.jpg\"></p>\n<p><img alt=\"Graphs\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/mscjkl5.jpg\"></p>\n<p>If you don’t wish to log height try this version of the shortcut.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://routinehub.co/shortcut/7969/\"><img alt=\"Log Weight &amp; Waist\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/kEO0fLF.png\"></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://routinehub.co/shortcut/7968/\"><img alt=\"Inhaler Usage\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/vDQ0OH3.p